properties.name: Recipe Process Event(1)
recipe process event configuration
properties.description: The Recipe Process Event Configuration is a name/value pair that describes the configuration of a Process Event, derived from Recipe that the Process Event's Production Run.  It is part of a set of configurations that contain information that the Production Run needs to communicate through its Process Events.

The Recipe Process Event Configuration describes the relationship between the Recipe and any Process Events which may be produced from a Production Run that uses that recipe.  Different Process Events have different properties depending on their type or the version of the recipe employed.
